b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29037.htm)  [Next](sbe29039.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KHA _N_ _D_ A 8.\n\n1 1. In the afternoon, having obtained by begging fried barley grains, he\nshall sacrifice them with his hand on the fire according to the rites of the \xc3\x82\n_g_ ya oblations with the text, 'The lord of the seat, the\n\np. 74\n\nwonderful' (Rig-veda I, 18, 6 seq.), verse by verse, down to the end of the\nhymn,\n\n2 8_2. Causing the teacher by (the gift of) food to pronounce auspicious\nwishes.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[73:1](sbe29038.htm#fr_162) 8, 1. This is the Anuprava _k_ aniyahoma treated\nof by \xc3\x82 _s_ valayana at I, 22, 12 seq. There it is stated that this sacrifice\nshould be performed as well after the recitation of the Savitri as after the\nother p. 74 portions of the Veda, for instance, as the commentary there has\nit, after the Mahanamnis, the Mahavrata, and the Upanishad have been recited.\nNaraya _n_ a indicates the time of this sacrifice in the words, 'On that same\nfast-day (chap. 7, 29) in the afternoon.'\n\n[74:8_2](sbe29038.htm#fr_163) 'He shall, by pronouncing such words as svasti\nbhavanto bruvantu, dispose the teacher favourably so that he may say svasti!'\nNaraya _n_ a.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 9](sbe29039.htm)\n\n"